\section*{Conclusion}
The experiment confirmed that inductors play a crucial role in limiting instantaneous changes in current. When the circuit was switched on, the LED did not light up instantly but instead brightened gradually. When the power supply was disconnected, the LED dimmed gradually as the inductor released its stored magnetic energy. This characteristic makes inductors essential in smoothing, filtering, and transient control in electronic circuits.

